                            <comment id="440238" author="sebastien" created="Mon, 6 Jan 2025 16:20:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is correct, patch &quot;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-16630&quot; title=&quot;Improve Kerberos cross-realm trust remapping&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-16630&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-16630&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; sec: improve Kerberos cross-realm trust remapping&quot; deprecated the use of idmap.conf, so we should move to the next level and remove support for it. Cross-realm trust remapping should be carried out via a mechanism provided by Kerberos, such as auth_to_local or equivalent.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
